
[1]abandoning

   ABAN'DONING, ppr. Forsaking or deserting wholly; renouncing; yielding
   one's self without restraint.

   ABAN'DONING, n. A forsaking; total desertion

   He hoped his past meritorious actions might outweigh his present
   abandoning the thought of future actions.
